        Task: Get news for Tesla and save to Notes/test_tesla.md
        
        Instructions:
        1. Use 'yahoo_finance' tools (get_stock_price, get_company_news) heavily.

extracted_tesla_news_summary_T002: Tesla's Q4 2023 earnings report showed a slight miss on revenue, with $25.17 billion compared to analyst expectations of $25.62 billion.
Net income for Q4 2023 was $7.93 billion, significantly boosted by a one-time tax benefit.
Automotive gross margin for Q4 2023 was 18.3%, down from 20.6% in the prior year.
The company delivered 484,507 vehicles in Q4 2023, a record for the quarter.
For the full year 2023, Tesla delivered 1.81 million vehicles.
Elon Musk indicated that the company is not planning any new vehicle model launches in 2024, focusing instead on production scaling of existing models like the Cybertruck and the refreshed Model 3.
Tesla aims to produce over 2 million vehicles in 2024.
The company anticipates a notable slowdown in year-over-year growth in 2024 compared to 2023.
Production of the Cybertruck is expected to ramp up significantly in 2024.

output.fallback_markdown:
## Tesla Q4 2023 Earnings and 2024 Outlook

**Financial Performance:**
- **Revenue Miss:** Tesla reported Q4 2023 revenue of $25.17 billion, falling slightly short of the $25.62 billion expected by analysts.
- **Net Income:** Net income for Q4 2023 reached $7.93 billion, largely due to a one-time tax benefit.
- **Automotive Gross Margin:** The automotive gross margin decreased to 18.3% in Q4 2023, compared to 20.6% in the same period last year.

**Vehicle Deliveries & Production:**
- **Q4 2023 Deliveries:** A record 484,507 vehicles were delivered in Q4 2023.
- **Full Year 2023 Deliveries:** Total deliveries for 2023 reached 1.81 million vehicles.
- **2024 Production Target:** Tesla aims to produce over 2 million vehicles in 2024.

**Strategic Focus & Outlook:**
- **No New Models in 2024:** Elon Musk stated that new vehicle model launches are not planned for 2024. The focus will be on scaling production of existing models, including the Cybertruck and the refreshed Model 3.
- **Cybertruck Ramp-Up:** Significant production ramp-up for the Cybertruck is anticipated in 2024.
- **Growth Slowdown:** Tesla expects a noticeable slowdown in year-over-year growth for 2024 compared to 2023.
output.formatted_report_T003:
Tesla Q4 2023 Earnings and 2024 Outlook

Key Takeaways: Tesla's Q4 2023 saw a slight revenue miss and a dip in automotive gross margin, despite record vehicle deliveries. The company anticipates a notable slowdown in year-over-year growth for 2024, with a strategic focus on scaling existing model production, particularly the Cybertruck, and no new model launches planned.

Financial Performance

Tesla's Q4 2023 financial results indicate a mixed performance with a slight miss on revenue expectations. While net income was significantly boosted by a one-time tax benefit, the automotive gross margin experienced a year-over-year decline.

  • Revenue: $25.17 billion (compared to analyst expectations of $25.62 billion), representing a slight miss.
  • Net Income: $7.93 billion (significantly boosted by a one-time tax benefit).
  • Automotive Gross Margin: 18.3% (down from 20.6% in the prior year).

Vehicle Deliveries and Production

The company achieved record vehicle deliveries in Q4 2023 and set ambitious production targets for the upcoming year. The focus remains on optimizing production of current and upcoming models.

  • Q4 2023 Deliveries: 484,507 vehicles (a record for the quarter).
  • Full Year 2023 Deliveries: 1.81 million vehicles.
  • 2024 Production Target: Aiming for over 2 million vehicles.

Strategic Focus and 2024 Outlook

Management has outlined a clear strategy for 2024, prioritizing production scaling over new model introductions. The ramp-up of the Cybertruck is a key operational focus.

  • New Vehicle Model Launches: No new vehicle model launches are planned for 2024.
  • Production Focus: Emphasis on scaling production of existing models, including the Cybertruck and the refreshed Model 3.
  • Cybertruck Production: Expected to ramp up significantly in 2024.
  • Year-over-Year Growth: Anticipation of a notable slowdown in growth compared to 2023.
Report generated based on available news data for Q4 2023 earnings and future outlook.
